.TH LU\-MULTI 1 "2026-04-27" "logicutils 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lu\-multi \- multicall dispatcher for the logicutils suite
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lu\-multi
\fIUTILITY\fR [\fIARG\fR...]
.br
.IB SYMLINK \fR (linked to \fBlu\-multi\fR) [\fIARG\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lu\-multi
is a busybox\-style multicall binary. When invoked through a symlink
whose name matches one of the bundled utilities
.RB ( freshcheck ", " stamp ", " lu\-match ", " lu\-expand ", "
.BR lu\-query ", " lu\-rule ", " lu\-queue ", " lu\-par ", " lu\-deps )
the request is dispatched to that utility. When invoked directly, the
first positional argument is treated as the utility name.

This single\-binary deployment is intended for resource\-constrained
environments such as embedded systems and busybox\-based images.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-list
Print the list of compiled\-in utilities and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Print a brief usage summary.
.SH EXIT STATUS
The exit status of the dispatched utility, or 2 if no utility could be
selected.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR freshcheck (1),
.BR stamp (1),
.BR lu\-match (1),
.BR lu\-expand (1),
.BR lu\-query (1),
.BR lu\-rule (1),
.BR lu\-queue (1),
.BR lu\-par (1),
.BR lu\-deps (1)
.SH AUTHOR
NEWSNIPER.
